    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Heads or highest parts of a mast of a ship, particularly the head of the lower mast used as a place for observation, or the highest part of the whole mast that is used as a place for flying a flag.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>船隻桅杆的上端或最高頂端，特別指較低桅杆上端，用以瞭望之處，又或指桅杆用來掛旗幟的頂端最高處。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De toppen of hoogste delen van scheepsmasten. De toppen van lage masten gebruikt men vaak voor observatie en in de toppen van hoge masten hangt men gewoonlijk een vlag.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
